 - partly rant </span><hr size=1> I am tired of starting newbie characters and still get lvl1 tattered armor drops off level 6th monsters.  Why can't those mobs drop studded, even if it is tattered studded.  I notice by the time I get a character up in levels, I may if lucky have about half the money of my casters.  Of course some of this money is lost due to repairing armor.<br>
<br>
Any way for a starting tank character to have it a little easier will be good.  I started a skald on Pendragon and at level 7, after doing all the newb quests I still cannot afford decent armor.  I had to buy bronze studded, got 7th quest bp and a weapon and down to 2 silver.  The bronze is blue and will be green at 8th and by the time I can afford iron I should be wearing steel.<br>
<br>
With low studded drops you would save all the tanks a lot of pain.  By the time you get to Nisse, if you even get any of the armor drops there, it will be green by 12.  <br>
<br>
Feel sorry for our warriors, chain drops from Nisse suck while Albs have chain drops from Mithra that is good until 17th not to mention they have nice bonuses.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the rant.  Seems as a skald I am constantly the main tank which is just to costly on armor and constitution hehe. <p>Palomide Server<br>Dragonsong 41stNorse Skald<br>Cavedragon 39th Troll Shaman<br>Dragonblades 26th Troll Berserker<br>Dragonstorm 11th Norse Thane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/28/02 4:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is not skald specific - partly rant </span><hr size=1> You have very valid points, but as for Skald being main tank.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Maybe you need to find a real tank for your group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uavelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avelan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/1/02 7:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is 